# Listeria monocytogenes WGS Analysis â€“ HackBio Stage 1

This repository contains the Bash scripts and outputs used for analyzing the **2017 South African Polony outbreak** isolates of *Listeria monocytogenes*.  
The workflow identifies organisms, screens for AMR genes, detects virulence factors, and proposes treatment implications.

---

## ðŸ”¬ Pipeline Overview

1. **Quality Control (FastQC / fastp)**
   - Raw reads assessed for quality, adapters trimmed.

2. **Genome Assembly (SPAdes)**
   ```bash
   spades.py -1 sample_1.fastq.gz -2 sample_2.fastq.gz -o spades_output
#Species confirmation using blast
blastn -query contigs.fasta -db nt -out blast_results.txt -outfmt 6

#AMR gene profiling
abricate --db card contigs.fasta > abricate_card_output.tab

#Virulence factor screening
abricate --db vfdb contigs.fasta > abricate_vfdb_output.tab

#Summaries
abricate --summary abricate_results/*.tab > abricate_matrix.tsv




